definitions.definition: A publication compiled by the graduating class of a high school or college , recording the year 's events and containing photographs of students and faculty .
A school subject in which students learn journalistic skills by compiling a yearbook.

main_definition: ( countable ) A reference book , published annually .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , US , education ) A publication compiled by the graduating class of a high school or college , recording the year 's events and containing photographs of students and faculty .
( uncountable , US , education ) A school subject in which students learn journalistic skills by compiling a yearbook.
